    "en": {
      "title": "Amber alert issued for strong winds & rough seas",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Meteorology Department has issued an amber alert for strong winds and rough seas, citing that wind speed can increase up to (55-60)\u00a0kmph in the sea areas off the coast\u00a0extending from Kankasanturai to\u00a0Puttalam and Matara to Pottuvil via\u00a0Hambantota.",
        "Accordingly, Wind speed can increase\u00a0up to 50 kmph in the sea areas off the\u00a0coast extending from Puttalam to Galle\u00a0via Colombo, while swell waves (about 2.0 \u2013 2.5) may\u00a0increase in the above-mentioned sea\u00a0areas and these sea areas will be rough.",
        "Naval and fishing communities have been requested to remain vigilant in this regard, and to remain\u00a0attentive to future\u00a0forecasts issued by the\u00a0Department of Meteorology in this\u00a0regard.",
        "Prof. Rangita De Silva De Alwis elected as SL representative for CEDAW",
        "Six people get addicted to heroin daily: National Authority on Tobacco and Alcohol"
      ],
